@mario I think we can pass the username in the URI, and then when we can do
Account newAccount = getUserAccountManager().getAccountByName({username})
I believe we need to establish the required URI format. Any ideas?
I'm thinking of "nc://directlink/f/{fileID}?username={username}", making username optional, which defaults to current user, by calling BaseActivity.getAccount(), but this potentially leads to problems as other users who gets the link might get totally different file when the fileID clashes
An alternative would be to make the username mandatory in forms like "nc://directlink/u/{username}/f/{fileID}", or maybe even "nc://directlink/{username}/f/{fileID}"

